		<h2 class="wprm-recipe-name wprm-block-text-none">Corned Venison</h2>
		<div class="wprm-recipe-summary wprm-block-text-normal"><span style="display: block;">So obviously this recipe works with all cervids, antelope, deer, moose, elk, etc. It will also work with beef and lamb, of course, but also bear and even pork -- where the effect is essentially a boiled ham. </span></div>
	</div>
