<p>thank you sir! This gave me another great way to silence the &#8220;venison is so gamey&#8221; critics. I had three bottom rounds (5 lbs total) from last years harvest that I usually save for jerky. I brine all 3 of them in the corned venison brine for 7 days. I finished 2 as corned beef and then coated one with the coriander and black pepper rub that you note in your pastrami recipe. I smoked it to an internal temp of 145. Both turned out wonderful. I really wish I could add pictures! I have read a lot about the difference between corned venison and pastrami is that after the brine the pastrami is smoked instead of simmered. Is this true? I noticed your pastrami recipe/brine is different. thanks again!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

