		<li id="comment-537964" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-537964" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">LH</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://honest-food.net/corned-venison-recipe/comment-page-13/#comment-537964" data-wpel-link="internal"><time datetime="2025-01-25T07:42:14-08:00">January 25, 2025 at 7:42 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Okay here’s an update. After the meat rested in the frig it was way better. I think it was the spice that smelled soapy not the cure. My spouse said it was great from day one but my sniffer is more sensitive. I still don’t like the idea of propylene glycol in my food, and I did have to make the slices thicker than the pics because it wa crumbly but tasted better after a day or two. I will try again and maybe modify the spice a little more to my liking.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-537964" data-commentid="537964" data-postid="17948" data-belowelement="div-comment-537964" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to LH" aria-label="Reply to LH">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-537817" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-537817" class="comment-body">
