		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-515770" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-515770" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Jason</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://honest-food.net/corned-venison-recipe/comment-page-13/#comment-515770" data-wpel-link="internal"><time datetime="2024-03-30T12:28:36-07:00">March 30, 2024 at 12:28 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I have a few really small venison roasts. 1 to 1.5 lbs.  Would your corned and pastrami recipes work with roasts this small?</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-515770" data-commentid="515770" data-postid="17948" data-belowelement="div-comment-515770" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jason" aria-label="Reply to Jason">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-515775" class="comment byuser comment-author-hank bypostauthor even depth-2 parent staff">
			<article id="div-comment-515775" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
