						<a href="https://honest-food.net/corned-venison-recipe/comment-page-13/#comment-515775" data-wpel-link="internal"><time datetime="2024-03-30T17:16:31-07:00">March 30, 2024 at 5:16 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Jason: Yes, it should work fine.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-515775" data-commentid="515775" data-postid="17948" data-belowelement="div-comment-515775" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Hank Shaw" aria-label="Reply to Hank Shaw">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-540576" class="comment odd alt depth-3">
			<article id="div-comment-540576" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Cars</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://honest-food.net/corned-venison-recipe/comment-page-13/#comment-540576" data-wpel-link="internal"><time datetime="2025-03-10T09:19:51-07:00">March 10, 2025 at 9:19 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I also have some smaller roasts. If I use this recipe with 2 2 lb roasts should I cure closer to the lower end (5 days) since the roasts are smaller? Or towards the longer end (7 days) since the total weight is larger?</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

